                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.712,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The second opinion by Justice Scalia is in case 13-9026 Whitfield v. Unites States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 8.712,
                                "stop": 14.357,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This case is here on writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.357,
                                "stop": 34.047,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It requires us to interpret Section 2113(e) of Title 18 of the United States Code which creates a mandatory minimum of 10 years imprisonment for anyone who \u201cforces any person to accompany him\u201d in the course of committing or fleeing from a bank robbery."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.047,
                                "stop": 44.876,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Larry Whitfield, the petitioner, was fleeing police after a botched bank robbery when he entered the home of 79-year-old Mary Parnell through an unlocked door."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 44.876,
                                "stop": 52.421,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Once inside he encountered a terrified Parnell and guided her from the hallway of her home to a computer room."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 52.421,
                                "stop": 61.483,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Whitfield estimates that he and Parnell in moving from the hallway to the computer room covered a distance of about 4-9 feet."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 61.483,
                                "stop": 65.452,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "There tragically Parnell had a heart attack and died."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.452,
                                "stop": 70.02,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Whitfield fled and the police found him hiding nearby."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.02,
                                "stop": 82.219,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "A grand jury indicted Whitfield for among other things violating Section 2113(e) by forcing Parnell to accompany him in the course of avoiding apprehension for a bank robbery."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.219,
                                "stop": 86.968,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Whitfield pleaded not guilty to the offense, but a jury convicted him."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.968,
                                "stop": 96.583,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "On appeal, Whitfield argued that 2113(e) requires substantial movement and that his movement with Parnell did not qualify."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 96.583,
                                "stop": 113.488,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Fourth Circuit disagreed holding that although Whitfield required Parnell \u201cto accompany him for only a short distance within her own home, and for a brief period, no more is required to prove that a forced accompaniment occurred.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.488,
                                "stop": 115.804,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We affirmed the Fourth Circuit\u0027s judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 115.804,
                                "stop": 126.566,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Congress enacted the forced accompaniment provision in 1934 and in 1934 justice today to accompany someone meant to go with him."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 126.566,
                                "stop": 133.023,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The word does not, as Whitfield contends, connote movement over a substantial distance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.023,
                                "stop": 142.977,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It was and is still perfectly natural to speak of accompanying someone over a short distance to the dinner table to the next room to the stage."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.977,
                                "stop": 153.025,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Whitfield is no doubt right that accompaniment does not embrace minimal movement, for example, the movement of a bank teller\u0027s feet when the robber grabs her arm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 153.025,
                                "stop": 164.127,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It must constitute movement that would normally be described as from one place to another, even if only from one spot within a room or outdoors to a different one."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 164.127,
                                "stop": 170.214,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Here however Whitfield forced Parnell to accompany him for at least several feet from one room to another."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 170.214,
                                "stop": 172.508,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That surely sufficed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.508,
                                "stop": 188.386,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We hold that a bank robber forces a person to accompany him for purposes of Section 2113(e) when he forces that person to go somewhere with him even if the movement occurs entirely within a single building or over a short distance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 188.386,
                                "stop": 192.995,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "To find in this manner Whitfield forced Parnell to accompany him."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 192.995,
                                "stop": 197.616,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The decision of the court is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
